## Architecture Principles

### 1. Safety-First Design
- **All operations containerized** - No direct system modification
- **Comprehensive input validation** - Defense against all attack vectors
- **Graceful degradation** - System continues operating under stress
- **Resource cleanup** - Automatic cleanup of all system resources

### 2. Reproducible Infrastructure
- **NixOS-only dependencies** - Guaranteed reproducible builds
- **Docker image consistency** - Identical environments across deployments
- **Version pinning** - Explicit versioning for all dependencies
- **Configuration as code** - Infrastructure defined declaratively

### 3. Modular Architecture
- **Single responsibility** - Each module has one clear purpose
- **Clean interfaces** - Well-defined module boundaries
- **Dependency injection** - Configurable dependencies
- **Composability** - Modules work together seamlessly

### 4. Performance by Design
- **Concurrent execution** - Leverages Erlang/OTP capabilities
- **Resource optimization** - Efficient memory and CPU usage
- **Connection pooling** - Database connection optimization
- **Caching strategies** - Multi-level caching implementation

### 5. Comprehensive Testing
- **100% functional coverage** - All code paths tested
- **Stress testing** - System pushed to breaking points
- **Security testing** - Attack vector resistance validation
- **Integration testing** - Real dependency validation

