- **Phase Tests**: Individual installation phase testing
- **Integration Tests**: Quick and full installation scenarios
- **Ash Framework Tests**: Project structure, domains, resources
- **API Tests**: GraphQL and JSON:API endpoint testing
- **Performance Tests**: Load testing, response time validation
- **Error Recovery Tests**: Failure recovery and cleanup

### Level 3: Implementation Details

#### 3.1 Test Environment Preparation
```elixir
@ash_test_modes [:ash_only, :ash_coverage, :ash_live, :ash_production]
@test_categories [
  "Infrastructure", "Phase", "Integration", "Ash Framework",
  "API", "Performance", "Error Recovery"
]

defp prepare_testing_environment do
  %{
    started_at: DateTime.utc_now(),
    mode: :testing,
    test_results: %{},
    tests_executed: 0,
    tests_passed: 0,
    tests_failed: 0,
    coverage_data: %{},
    performance_metrics: %{},
    errors: [],
    warnings: []
  }
end
```

#### 3.2 Test Execution Strategies
```elixir
# Sequential Testing
defp execute_sequential_testing(report, opts, image_info) do
  Enum.reduce_while(@ash_test_modes, report, fn test_mode, acc_report ->
    case execute_single_test_mode(acc_report, test_mode, opts, image_info) do
      {:ok, updated_report} -> {:cont, updated_report}
      {:error, reason} -> {:halt, {:error, reason}}
    end
  end)
end

# Parallel Testing  
defp execute_parallel_testing(report, opts, image_info) do
  tasks = Enum.map(@ash_test_modes, fn test_mode ->
    Task.async(fn -> execute_single_test_mode(report, test_mode, opts, image_info) end)
  end)
  
  results = Task.await_many(tasks, 600_000)
  compile_comprehensive_report(report, results, opts)
end
```

#### 3.3 Test Script Generation System
```elixir
defp generate_test_script(test_mode, opts) do
  case test_mode do
    :ash_only -> Validation.generate_ash_test_script("ash_only", opts)
    :ash_coverage -> Validation.generate_ash_test_script("ash_coverage", opts)
    :ash_live -> Validation.generate_ash_test_script("ash_live", opts)
    :ash_production -> Validation.generate_ash_test_script("ash_production", opts)
  end
end
```

### Level 4: Internal Mechanisms

#### 4.1 Test Timeout Management
```elixir
@base_timeouts %{
  ash_only: 180_000,        # 3 minutes
  ash_coverage: 300_000,    # 5 minutes  
  ash_live: 600_000,        # 10 minutes
  ash_production: 900_000   # 15 minutes
}

defp determine_test_timeout(test_mode, opts) do
  base_timeout = Map.get(@base_timeouts, test_mode, 300_000)
  if opts[:extended], do: base_timeout * 2, else: base_timeout
end
```

#### 4.2 Result Analysis Engine
```elixir
defp analyze_test_results(results) do
  Enum.split_with(results, fn {_mode, result} ->
    case result do
      {:ok, _} -> true
      _ -> false
    end
  end)
end
```

#### 4.3 Comprehensive Report Generation
- **Test summary**: Pass/fail counts, duration, success rate
- **Individual results**: Detailed results for each test mode
- **Performance metrics**: Response times, resource usage
- **Recommendations**: Based on test outcomes and failures

#### 4.4 Report Output Formats
- **Console output**: Real-time progress and summary
- **Markdown reports**: Detailed analysis with timestamps
- **JSON data**: Machine-readable test results
- **Performance charts**: Visual performance metrics

## 6. Intelitor.Logger Module

### Level 1: Module Overview

**Purpose**: Comprehensive logging system for all installation scripts and operations
**Responsibilities**: Activity tracking, metric collection, error logging, audit trails
**Dependencies**: File system, JSON encoding (optional)
**Interfaces**: Structured logging API with multiple log levels

### Level 2: Functional Architecture

#### 2.1 Logging Architecture
```
Log Input → Level Filter → Format → Multiple Outputs (File + Console) → Rotation
```

#### 2.2 Logging Levels and Categories
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                              Logging System                                │
├─────────────────┬─────────────────┬─────────────────┬─────────────────────┤
│     Levels      │   Categories    │    Outputs      │     Features        │
│                 │                 │                 │                     │
│ • DEBUG         │ • Activity      │ • File Logs     │ • Rotation          │
│ • INFO          │ • Metrics       │ • Console       │ • Structured Data   │  
│ • WARN          │ • Claude Ops    │ • JSON Export   │ • Session Tracking  │
│ • ERROR         │ • Script Exec   │ • Audit Trail   │ • Performance       │
│ • FATAL         │ • System Ops    │                 │                     │
└─────────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────────┘
```

#### 2.3 Specialized Logging Functions
- **Activity Tracking**: Start/end activity with unique IDs
- **Metric Collection**: Performance and usage metrics
- **Claude Operations**: AI assistant activity logging
- **Script Execution**: Complete script lifecycle tracking
- **System Operations**: Infrastructure and deployment logging

### Level 3: Implementation Details

#### 3.1 Logger Configuration Structure
```elixir
defstruct [
  :log_level,      # :debug | :info | :warn | :error | :fatal
  :log_to_file,    # boolean - enable file logging
  :log_to_stdout,  # boolean - enable console logging  
  :context,        # string - logging context identifier
  :session_id,     # string - unique session identifier
  :start_time      # DateTime - session start time
]

@log_dir "./log"
@log_file "installation.log"
@activity_log_file "activity.log"
@max_log_size_mb 50
@max_log_files 10
```

#### 3.2 Core Logging Implementation
```elixir
def log(config, level, message, metadata) do
  if should_log?(config.log_level, level) do
    log_entry = %{
      timestamp: DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_iso8601(),
      level: level,
      session_id: config.session_id,
      context: config.context,
      message: message,
      metadata: metadata
    }
    
    formatted = format_log_entry(log_entry)
    
    if config.log_to_stdout, do: IO.puts(formatted)
    if config.log_to_file, do: append_to_log_file(formatted)
  end
end
```

#### 3.3 Activity Tracking System
```elixir
def start_activity(config, activity_name, metadata \\ %{}) do
  activity_id = generate_activity_id()
  
  entry = %{
    type: :activity_start,
    activity_id: activity_id,
    activity_name: activity_name,
    started_at: DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_iso8601(),
    metadata: metadata
  }
  
  log_activity(config, entry)
  {config, activity_id}
end
```

### Level 4: Internal Mechanisms

#### 4.1 Log Rotation Engine
```elixir
defp rotate_logs do
  # Rotate existing logs (N -> N+1)
  for i <- (@max_log_files - 1)..1 do
    old_path = Path.join(@log_dir, "#{@log_file}.#{i}")
    new_path = Path.join(@log_dir, "#{@log_file}.#{i + 1}")
    
    if File.exists?(old_path) do
      if i + 1 >= @max_log_files do
        File.rm!(old_path)  # Delete oldest
      else
        File.rename!(old_path, new_path)  # Rotate
      end
    end
  end
  
  # Move current log to .1
  current_path = Path.join(@log_dir, @log_file)
  if File.exists?(current_path) do
    File.rename!(current_path, Path.join(@log_dir, "#{@log_file}.1"))
  end
end
```

#### 4.2 Session ID Generation
```elixir
defp generate_session_id do
  :crypto.strong_rand_bytes(8) |> Base.encode16(case: :lower)
end

defp generate_activity_id do
  :crypto.strong_rand_bytes(4) |> Base.encode16(case: :lower)  
end
```

#### 4.3 Environment Sanitization
```elixir
defp sanitize_env(env) do
  sensitive_keys = ["PASSWORD", "TOKEN", "KEY", "SECRET", "CREDENTIAL"]
  
  env
  |> Enum.filter(fn {k, _v} ->
    key_upper = String.upcase(to_string(k))
    not Enum.any?(sensitive_keys, &String.contains?(key_upper, &1))
  end)
  |> Enum.into(%{})
end
```

#### 4.4 System Information Collection
```elixir
defp gather_system_info do
  %{
    hostname: System.cmd("hostname", []) |> elem(0) |> String.trim(),
    os: :os.type() |> elem(0) |> to_string(),
    cpu_count: System.schedulers_online(),
    memory_mb: get_memory_info(),
    elixir_version: System.version(),
    erlang_version: :erlang.system_info(:otp_release) |> to_string(),
    timestamp: DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_iso8601()
  }
end
```

